title: Malik Iftikhar of PML(N) wins PP-14 Rawalpindi election
content:
ISLAMABAD, Feb 9 (APP): Malik Iftikhar of the Pakistan Muslim League-Nawaz (PML-N) has won the election for Punjab Assembly constituency PP-14 Rawalpindi by securing 40148 votes.
According to the unofficial result issued by the Returning Officer/ECP, his runner-up was Ali Khan, an independent candidate who bagged 33487 votes.
Votersâ€™ turnout remained 56 percent.
